Major refactor: modularize app, add security, template inheritance, logging

- Split monolithic app.py (6500 lines) into route blueprints and service modules
  routes/: auth, dashboard, payments, webhook, admin, pages
  services/: auth, users, email, ai, instagram, stripe_handlers, subscription, messaging, activity
- Add CSRF protection (flask-wtf) on all POST forms, exempt webhooks
- Add admin_required decorator; protect all /admin/* routes with user ID check
- Gate debug routes behind DEBUG_ROUTES_ENABLED env var
- Fail on default SECRET_KEY in production
- Create base.html with Jinja2 template inheritance; all 18 templates now extend it
- Extract shared CSS into static/css/common.css and JS into static/js/common.js
- Add PostgreSQL connection pooling (psycopg2.pool.SimpleConnectionPool)
- Replace all print() with structured Python logging (configurable LOG_LEVEL)
- Extract magic numbers into Config constants (STARTER/STANDARD_MONTHLY_REPLIES, ADDON_REPLIES, BASE_URL, SUPPORT_EMAIL)
- Pin all dependency versions in requirements.txt
- Delete dead files (cube.html, test_railway_connection.py, update_db.py, update_instagram_id.py, SIMPLE_STEPS.txt, WEBHOOK_SIGNATURE_TIMELINE.md)
